description.narrative: (Kenya): The Kenya Health Information System collects routine data at the health facility level via the District Health Information System (DHIS2) platform, which is the key data source for the National Malaria Control and Reproductive, Maternal, Newborn and Child Health (RMNCH) programs. Using FY2015 funds, this activity will:In select counties, strengthen the Health Information System and the collection of information at the health facility, sub-county and county levels. Improvements will be monitored through data quality audits. The investments will help improve the quality of data collected to inform decision-making for the National Malaria Control and RMNCH programs at all levels.
